resource.description: DIAGNOSTIC ARTHROSCOPY OF KNEE WITHOUT SYNOVIAL BIOPSY - Left with Physician Orthopaedics, MD in EMH OR on 11/16/2013
resource.patientInstruction:
ARTHROSCOPY KNEE
Here are some basic reminders about your Arthroscopy with Dr. Orthopedics 
1. Be sure to not eat after midnight the night before your surgery. Doing so may require that we delay your procedure. If you have questions, be sure to the nurse at Dr. Orthopedics' office at (608)271-9000. 
2. Bring all of the medications that you are currently taking or that you have recently taken. Dr. Orthopedics will make sure that you are prescribed the appropriate medications after your Arthroscopy. 
3. It's important to arrange transportation to and from the hospital/clinic. You will not be in a position to drive yourself after the surgery. The nurse will ask for your travel arrangements when you arrive. 
4. Please don't bring any unnecessary valuables with you. Jewelry, MP3 players, watches, cell phones should all be left home if appropriate. 

If you are unable to make your surgery date, please call Dr. Orthopedics' nurse (608-271-9000) as soon as possible.
